- Analogy: Think of EBS as network USB sticks

- Network drive you can attach to your instances while they run
- It allows your instances to persist data, even after their termination
- They can be mounted to once instance at a time (at CCP level)
- Bound to a specific availability zone
- Free tier 30 GB of free per month

- Its a network drive not a physical drive
- Uses a network to communicate, which means potential latency.
- It can be detatched from the EC2 instance and attached to another one quickly
- It is locked to availability zones
- To Move you must snapshot first